article.headline: Liberty 92, Houghton College 46
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Liberty scored almost three times as many points in the first half as Houghton and then cruised to a 92-46 victory Saturday night. Alex McLean scored 26 points and Larry Blair had 24 for Liberty, which shot 50.7 percent from the field. Houghton led briefly in the opening minutes and were hanging close until McLean hit a free throw with 11:58 left in the first half. Seconds later, McLean made a jumper that kicked off 20 unanswered points -- including two 3-pointers by B.J. Jenkins -- for the Flames (2-1) to put them up 36-11 with 8:09 left in the half. The Highlanders (1-2) came out of the locker room for the second half facing a 53-18 deficit. Rell Porter had 10 points and two steals for Liberty. Damien Hubbard added three steals. Luke Mortenson scored 11 points for Houghton.
